data.body:
- VSCode Version: 1.6.1
- OS Version: Windows 7 32-bit (and at least partially in Windows 10 64-bit)

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create two empty text documents (call them _A_ and _B_);
2. Create two shortcuts (call them _C_ which links to _A_, and _D_ which links to _B_);
3. Select _A_ and _B_, right click on _A_ or _B_, then select “Open with Code”;
4. _A_ and _B_ are opened normally. This is expected.
5. Select _C_ and _D_, right click on _C_ or _D_, then select “Open with Code”;
6. **Only one of _A_ and _B_ is opened while both of them should be opened.**
7. Select _A_ and _C_, right click on _A_, then select “Open with Code”;
8. **_A_ and _C_ are opened, while only _A_ should be opened since they are the same file.**
9. Select _A_ and _C_, right click on _C_, then select “Open with Code”;
10. _A_ is opened. This is expected.
11. Select _A_ and _D_, right click on _A_, then select “Open with Code”;
12. **_A_ and _D_ are opened, while both _A_ and _B_ should be opened.**
13. Select _A_ and _D_, right click on _D_, then select “Open with Code”;
14. **Only _B_ is opened, while both _A_ and _B_ should be opened.**
